1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses novel transmission modes based on amplify-and-forward, which is a common technique in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless systems and communication flows, which are key topics in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the role of the relay in managing interference and boosting system performance, which is related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of multiple antennas and beamforming, which are techniques commonly used in multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper involves optimization of relay precoding, which is a computational problem and can be related to computational engineering.
